Hu Jintao Stresses Need for Qualified Officials
BEIJING , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- Hu Jintao , a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China ( CPC ) , stressed here today that greater efforts must be made to foster more qualified Chinese officials who will offer strong organizational backing to the implementation of central policies .
The remark was made while Hu , who is also president of the Party School of the CPC Central Committee , delivered a speech at the graduation ceremony for 62 officials at the provincial and ministerial level who had completed a course of advanced study .
He noted that strong leadership of the CPC Central Committee and a contingent of qualified officials will be conducive to the success of China 's reform , opening-up and modernization drive .
He asked leading officials at all levels to launch an in-depth study of Deng Xiaoping Theory and educate officials with the Party 's spirit and style focusing on study , politics and a healthy atmosphere .
Moreover , leading officials at all levels must adhere to the principle of democratic centralism , uphold the authority of the central government , and carry out the Party 's guidelines and policies to the letter , he said .
Hu also demanded the intensification of reform of the personnel system to select more capable officials on an equal basis , and required leading officials to be self-disciplined and maintain their demeanor as civil servants of the people .
